{"id": 231951082, "title": "Support worker who attacked colleague at Christmas party before being arrested given warning", "text": "A support worker has been given a warning after attacking a colleague during a work Christmas party. Leeanne Allen was employed as a supporter worker at Community Lifestyles in Glasgow in December 2021 when the incident unfolded at a residential party. Allen was found to have struck a colleague on the face and head and grabbed her by the hair. She was then arrested and given a Fiscal fine. The behaviour led to the victim being \u201cphysically and emotionally\u201d harmed. Allen was reported to the Scottish Social Services Council who found at Allen had been \u201cdrinking too much and mixing alcoholic drinks\u201d leading to actions which demonstrated a \u201clack of control\u201d. Their report added: \u201cYou have behaved in a violent manner and you caused physical and emotional harm to acolleague. \u201cYou have failed to provide the SSSC with assurances that you have understood and regret the impact your behaviour had on your colleague.\u201d The SSSC decided to allow Allen to continue to work in the profession but imposed a 12 month warning on her registration.", "summary": "Leeanne Allen was arrested after 'mixing alcoholic drinks' and attacking a colleague in December 2021.", "url": "https://news.stv.tv/west-central/support-worker-who-attacked-colleague-at-christmas-party-before-being-arrested-given-warning", "image": "https://news.stv.tv/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/4ef455d0f188872b5ca0504afa0444a6-1707822130.jpg", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-09 12:40:45", "author": "Holly Lennon", "authors": ["Holly Lennon"], "language": "en", "source_country": "tv", "sentiment": -0.555}